author: George Beasley
reviewText: Browse Github Octodroid is the best Github explorer I've used on Android. View Readme's, Source files, open links, in line video/gif support. Everything you need is here in a nice material design interface.

author: Florian Kaiser
reviewText: GitHub Enterprise Please add support for GitHub Enterprise!

author: xete FiRe
reviewText: Some advice hoping to be taken advice for optimizations: 1) the row above could be designed to be smaller,with reading area larger 2) 'search' can be divided to get certain, which would now be long under poor network circumtances

author: Mokhdzani Faeq
reviewText: nice app the trending feature is not working though. 5 star if you fix that

author: Daniel Strom
reviewText: Great app Missing support for tables in markdown. A menu link to the GitHub pages for any given project would be nice, if the gh-pages branch exists.

author: Maarten Fonville
reviewText: Best github app available. 1 small request: under releases->downloads the downloads are shown in a very small scrollable frame. If this frame could be enlarged to show all downloads and enable scrolling for the whole screen, that would be great!

author: Vicky Chijwani
reviewText: Shouldn't need my password Github supports OAuth, which means I should be able to sign in on the Github website securely rather than having to trust some random app with my password. Just saying "app doesn't store password" in the description is NOT ENOUGH.

author: David Thomas
reviewText: Better login needed App should open a webpage in my phone's browser to authorize to GitHub. I don't trust random apps with my password if the provider supports Oauth. Change this, please.

author: Neil Scudder
reviewText: Great fonts, awkward navigation Should use oauth login. No code highlighting for golang :( Why does it need access to files?
